    <div class="section">
      <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> February 1, 2026</p>
      <p>Your privacy is important to us. This policy explains how Slack Meet Command collects, uses, and protects your information.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="info-box">
      <h3>Privacy-First Approach</h3>
      <p>We believe in minimal data collection. We only collect what's absolutely necessary to provide the Service, and we never sell your data.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      
      <h3>1.1 Authentication Data</h3>
      <p>When you authenticate with Google:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google OAuth tokens</strong> - Stored securely to create meeting spaces on your behalf</li>
        <li><strong>Slack user ID and team ID</strong> - To associate your Google credentials with your Slack identity</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>What we DON'T access:</strong> Your calendar, emails, contacts, or any other Google data beyond meeting space creation.</p>

      <h3>1.2 Usage Analytics (Optional)</h3>
      <p>If Google Analytics is enabled, we collect anonymous usage data:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Page visits</strong> - When users view the homepage</li>
        <li><strong>Authentication events</strong> - When OAuth is completed (no personal info)</li>
        <li><strong>/meet command usage</strong> - Frequency and whether a title was provided (not the actual title)</li>
        <li><strong>Anonymous user identifier</strong> - MD5 hash of user_id+team_id (irreversible, used for usage patterns)</li>
        <li><strong>Geographic location</strong> - Country level only (IP is anonymized)</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>What we DON'T track:</strong> Your actual user IDs, names, emails, meeting titles, or any personally identifiable information (PII).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>OAuth tokens</strong> - To create Google Meet links when you use the <code>/meet</code> command</li>
        <li><strong>Usage analytics</strong> - To understand how the Service is used and improve it (aggregate data only)</li>
        <li><strong>Error logs</strong> - To diagnose and fix technical issues (minimal data, automatically deleted)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>3. Data Storage and Security</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>OAuth tokens are stored in an encrypted database</li>
        <li>All communication uses HTTPS encryption</li>
        <li>Tokens are automatically refreshed when needed</li>
        <li>We implement industry-standard security practices</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties, except:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google</strong> - To authenticate and create meeting spaces (required for Service functionality)</li>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> - Anonymous usage statistics (if enabled, opt-in only)</li>
        <li><strong>Legal requirements</strong> - If required by law or to protect our rights</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Revoke access</strong> - Disconnect your Google account at any time via Google account settings</li>
        <li><strong>Data deletion</strong> - Request deletion of your stored OAuth tokens</li>
        <li><strong>Access your data</strong> - Request information about what data we store about you</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="https://alessiosignorini.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">alessiosignorini.com</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>OAuth tokens are stored until you revoke access or stop using the Service</li>
        <li>Usage analytics data is retained according to Google Analytics policies (26 months by default)</li>
        <li>We do not store meeting titles, content, or participant information</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>7. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>This Service integrates with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google Meet</strong> - Subject to <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><strong>Slack</strong> - Subject to <a href="https://slack.com/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Slack's Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> - Subject to <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's Privacy Policy</a> (if enabled)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>This Service is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children.</p>
